Beyond imaging, AI has accelerated drug discovery by analyzing molecular structures and predicting compound interactions much faster than traditional methods. Predictive analytics enables early identification of patients at high risk for conditions like heart disease and diabetes by analyzing electronic health records and genetic information. This allows healthcare providers to intervene with preventive care earlier, potentially saving lives and reducing costs through proactive measures rather than reactive treatment.

